    "name": "DERS-SF Difficulties in Emotion Regulation Scale",
    "fullName": "Difficulties in Emotion Regulation Scale-Short Form",
    "description": "The DERS-SF is an 18-item short form assessing difficulties in emotion regulation across 6 dimensions: nonacceptance of emotional responses, difficulties engaging in goal-directed behavior, impulse control difficulties, lack of emotional awareness, limited access to emotion regulation strategies, and lack of emotional clarity.",
    "author": "Kaufman et al. (2016)",
    "license": "Free to use",
    "reference": "Kaufman EA, Xia M, Fosco G, et al. The Difficulties in Emotion Regulation Scale Short Form (DERS-SF). J Psychopathol Behav Assess. 2016;38(3):443-455.",
